OL,6,FHe said: "He held down a full time
OL,7,Fjob, he had a wife and two small
OL,8,Fchildren. By all accounts, he was a
OL,9,Fnormal person - but online he was a
OL,10,Fvery different person completely; a
OL,11,Fmonster exploiting a young girl."
OL,13,FOn one occasion, "Mark" told her that
OL,14,Fthe other men owed him money, and
OL,15,Fwould stay away from her if he said
OL,16,Fso, the court heard.
OL,18,FHe told the victim that one of the
OL,19,Fpersonas would "argue with his own
OL,20,Freflection".
